  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting refugees and migrants through a consolidated Mediterranean and flow-monitoring response in Turkey</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project IOM will provide humanitarian assistance to refugees and migrants rescued at sea and continue to operationalize IOM&#x2019;s Migrant Presence Monitoring (MPM) program, a displacement monitoring and reporting system which provides a regular overview and update on the flows, locations, and vulnerabilities of migrants and refugees in Turkey. The delivery of humanitarian assistance will be focused on the provision of food items, non-food items (NFIs), counselling including psycho-social support (PSS), and referrals to protection services for migrants and refugees rescued at sea (border zone between Turkey and Greece) - more specifically along the coastal area between K&#xFC;&#xE7;&#xFC;kkuyu and Bodrum.</narrative>
  </description>
